            "id": "4579373",
            "title": "Metaplanet issues ¥8B bonds for BTC; zero-yield hits shares",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Metaplanet (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MTPLF\" title=\"Metaplanet Inc.\">MTPLF</a></span>) announced on Friday that it will issue its 20th series of ordinary bonds worth ¥8B to EVO FUND. The main purpose of raising this fund is to buy more Bitcoin (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BTC-USD\" title=\"Bitcoin USD\">BTC-USD</a>).</p>\n<p>Each bond has a face value of ¥200.00M and carries zero interest, meaning investors won’t earn periodic returns. The bonds will be issued on April 24, 2026, and will be fully repaid at face value on April 23, 2027, according to the <a href=\"https://contents.xj-storage.jp/xcontents/33500/1758d044/285f/4e65/93c0/04d9b3d9af96/140120260424510122.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"official filing\">official filing</a>.</p>\n<p data-end=\"374\" data-start=\"111\">The company can also repay the bonds early if the bondholder gives a 5-day notice or under certain future financing conditions. These bonds are unsecured, meaning there is no collateral or guarantee. Moreover, the full bond issue is allocated only to EVO FUND.</p>\n<p data-end=\"655\" data-start=\"376\">Currently, <span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Metaplanet (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MTPLF\" title=\"Metaplanet Inc.\">MTPLF</a>)</span> <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4874389-metaplanet-bet-on-bitcoin-and-the-mnav\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"holds about ~40.18K BTC\">holds about ~40.18K BTC</a>, which is roughly ~0.91% of Bitcoin’s total supply. This makes it the third-largest corporate Bitcoin (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BTC-USD\" title=\"Bitcoin USD\">BTC-USD</a>) holder, after <span class=\"whitespace-normal\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4577933-saylors-setup-uncovered-inside-strategys-28b-gain-at-79k-btc\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"MicroStrategy\">MicroStrategy</a></span> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSTR\" title=\"Strategy Inc\">MSTR</a>) and <span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Twenty One Capital (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XXI\" title=\"Twenty One Capital, Inc.\">XXI</a>)</span>.</p>\n<p data-end=\"773\" data-start=\"657\">After the announcement, MTPLF stock fell to ~¥339, down around ~4% from the previous close of ~¥352. The company expects this bond issuance to have a mild impact on its FY26 financial results.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
