            "id": "4579188",
            "title": "Wall Street mixed as Israel-Lebanon truce gets extended",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\" data-end=\"143\" data-start=\"0\">The stock market opened mixed on Friday as the ceasefire between Israel and Lebanon got extended by three weeks. </p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>The S&amp;P 500 (</span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SP500#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Index\"><span>SP500</span></a><span>) +0.2%, the Dow (</span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DJI#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"Dow Jones Industrial Average Index\"><span>DJI</span></a><span>) -0.3%, and the Nasdaq Composite (</span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COMP:IND#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\" title=\"NASDAQ Composite Index\"><span>COMP:IND</span></a><span>) +0.6%. </span></p>\n<p data-end=\"634\" data-start=\"315\">President <span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Donald Trump</span> said in a social media post that he had ordered the U.S. Navy to “shoot and kill any boat” caught laying mines in the strait.</p>\n<p data-end=\"832\" data-start=\"636\">Treasury yields edged slightly lower across the curve. The 2-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) dipped to 3.84%, while the 10-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) eased to 4.33%. The 30-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US30Y\" title=\"United States 30-Year Bond Yield\">US30Y</a>) also inched down to 4.91%.</p>\n<p data-end=\"988\" data-start=\"834\">The economic calendar for the day includes the consumer sentiment report. </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
